00:01:02.620 --> 00:01:05.050
But, obviously, we
have-- a lot of the year,

00:01:05.050 --> 00:01:07.530
we're on the sidelines
just hanging out.

00:01:07.530 --> 00:01:10.220
Now, I know a lot of you
might not be snowboarders.

00:01:10.220 --> 00:01:12.040
So what I'm about
to show you, you

00:01:12.040 --> 00:01:13.990
might not grasp
the full reality,

00:01:13.990 --> 00:01:15.040
the full gravity of that.

00:01:15.040 --> 00:01:17.680
So if you could just, for a
moment, think about something

00:01:17.680 --> 00:01:22.280
that is an activity that you
can only enjoy five days a year.

00:01:22.280 --> 00:01:25.900
Maybe it's traveling,
like a fishing trip maybe

00:01:25.900 --> 00:01:27.612
or climbing a mountain.

00:01:27.612 --> 00:01:29.320
Think about-- think
about that experience

00:01:29.320 --> 00:01:35.570
for a second and those feelings
that you have enjoying this.

00:01:35.570 --> 00:01:38.360
And, now, imagine
if somebody told you

00:01:38.360 --> 00:01:40.760
you can enjoy this experience
and have these feelings

00:01:40.760 --> 00:01:45.750
on demand anywhere in the world,
after work, on the weekends,

00:01:45.750 --> 00:01:46.950
whenever you want.

00:01:46.950 --> 00:01:49.820
That's basically what we've
done for snowboarders.

00:01:49.820 --> 00:01:52.640
And so what is it
about snowboarding

00:01:52.640 --> 00:01:55.190
that makes it so incredible?

00:01:55.190 --> 00:02:01.190
And it's a combination of
speed, and turning, and carving,

00:02:01.190 --> 00:02:04.950
which is leaning
into your carves--

00:02:04.950 --> 00:02:05.960
your turns rather.

00:02:05.960 --> 00:02:08.870
But it's this controlled
drift, I think,

00:02:08.870 --> 00:02:11.510
that is really that
addicting part.

00:02:11.510 --> 00:02:14.720
And the drift, it's
something that, you know,

00:02:14.720 --> 00:02:18.050
from the first time you ran and
slid across your kitchen floor,

00:02:18.050 --> 00:02:21.320
or drifted out the
back tire of your bike

00:02:21.320 --> 00:02:24.530
or your scooter as a
kid, or doing donuts

00:02:24.530 --> 00:02:26.250
around your high
school parking lot,

00:02:26.250 --> 00:02:28.960
there's something just
addicting about that.

00:02:28.960 --> 00:02:31.850
And snowboarding is
really unique because it--

00:02:31.850 --> 00:02:35.120
it takes that drift and
puts you in total control,

00:02:35.120 --> 00:02:37.400
and so you can spin,
and you can slide.

00:02:37.400 --> 00:02:40.970
And there's really just
nothing else like it.

00:02:40.970 --> 00:02:44.210
And so that is just so unique
to snowboarding and something

00:02:44.210 --> 00:02:46.760
that has just never
existed anywhere else.

00:02:46.760 --> 00:02:48.440
Another great thing
about snowboarding

00:02:48.440 --> 00:02:51.290
is that community aspect,
so sharing this adrenaline

00:02:51.290 --> 00:02:55.617
with your friends and going
out and snowboarding with them.

00:02:55.617 --> 00:02:57.950
And sometimes, you know, given
that snowboarding is just

00:02:57.950 --> 00:03:00.200
a five-day-a-year experience,
you might only see these

00:03:00.200 --> 00:03:02.870
friends five days a
year or, at least,

00:03:02.870 --> 00:03:06.591
just enjoying this experience
with them for only five days.

00:03:06.591 --> 00:03:08.090
And so all of these
things together,

00:03:08.090 --> 00:03:10.760
snowboarding can be a little
bit of a frustrating sport

00:03:10.760 --> 00:03:12.710
most of the year.

00:03:12.710 --> 00:03:14.530
And so that's what
we set out to change.

00:03:14.530 --> 00:03:17.020
And we are a group
of snowboarders

00:03:17.020 --> 00:03:20.200
that all share that dream
of riding all year around.

00:03:20.200 --> 00:03:23.680
And I can tell you
getting to that point

00:03:23.680 --> 00:03:26.320
where we can enjoy the sport
all year round as a snowboarder,

00:03:26.320 --> 00:03:29.750
it really is a dream come true.

00:03:29.750 --> 00:03:32.240
And so what does it look like?

00:03:32.240 --> 00:03:34.390
It's kind of hard to
describe in words,

00:03:34.390 --> 00:03:37.720
somebody actually snowboarding
in Dubai or around the world.

00:03:37.720 --> 00:03:41.100
So I'll just show you a quick
video that'll show the--

00:03:41.100 --> 00:03:43.840
the capabilities of the LEIF.

00:03:43.840 --> 00:03:45.820
