00:20:42.370 --> 00:20:44.414
How often do they have
to replace the wheels?

00:20:44.414 --> 00:20:45.830
AARON ADERS: Really
good question.

00:20:45.830 --> 00:20:49.090
So in skateboarding,
you have a couple

00:20:49.090 --> 00:20:51.010
of factors that go
into your wheels.

00:20:51.010 --> 00:20:53.690
One is kind of rebound,
how bouncy it is.

00:20:53.690 --> 00:20:57.060
Another one is called durometer,
which is how hard it is.

00:20:57.060 --> 00:20:59.770
And so they have durometer from,
like, you know, like, jelly,

00:20:59.770 --> 00:21:01.600
all the way to hard plastic.

00:21:01.600 --> 00:21:04.400
And the skateboard wheels
fall somewhere in between.

00:21:04.400 --> 00:21:07.480
And so the harder
durometer will last longer

00:21:07.480 --> 00:21:09.990
because it just resists that--

00:21:09.990 --> 00:21:11.650
that abrasion a
little bit better.

00:21:11.650 --> 00:21:14.770
And, also, it slides
better because it's not

00:21:14.770 --> 00:21:16.480
gripping that pavement.

00:21:16.480 --> 00:21:20.622
And so we use a bit harder
durometer wheels than probably

00:21:20.622 --> 00:21:21.580
the average skateboard.

00:21:21.580 --> 00:21:24.430
A skateboarder would consider
our wheels a bit hard

00:21:24.430 --> 00:21:25.712
on that durometer side.

00:21:25.712 --> 00:21:27.670
But, again, it kind of
works with that sliding,

00:21:27.670 --> 00:21:29.920
and it lasts a lot longer.

00:21:29.920 --> 00:21:33.280
And, also, a key, so you
can tell a little bit

00:21:33.280 --> 00:21:34.400
in this image.

00:21:34.400 --> 00:21:38.020
So the outside of the wheels
are kind of getting dirty,

00:21:38.020 --> 00:21:39.700
and they start to cone.

00:21:39.700 --> 00:21:42.280
And so whenever you
get too much wear,

00:21:42.280 --> 00:21:44.790
you just flip the
wheel 180 degrees.

00:21:44.790 --> 00:21:46.720
And then you start
working on the other side.

00:21:46.720 --> 00:21:48.490
And then you flip it again,
and you flip it again,

00:21:48.490 --> 00:21:50.260
and you might get
six flips before you

00:21:50.260 --> 00:21:52.000
have to change the wheels.

00:21:52.000 --> 00:21:55.750
When I had-- it was a
five mile round-m trip

00:21:55.750 --> 00:21:59.500
commute in Brooklyn, a set of
wheels, when flipped regularly,

00:21:59.500 --> 00:22:02.090
would last about six months.

